Wash and dry all produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @apple{1}. Strip @thyme{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; mince leaves until you have 2 tsp (3 tsp for 4 servings).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add apple; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add @sugar{1/2%tsp}, minced thyme, and @water{1%tbsp}. Cook, stirring, until apple is caramelized and jammy, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Turn off heat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}; transfer to a #small bowl{}.

== Sandwiches ==

Place @sourdough bread{4%slices} on a clean work surface. Spread half the slices with @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, then top with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}, caramelized apple, and @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}. Place remaining bread slices on top to create sandwiches.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in pan used for apple over medium heat. Add sandwiches and cook until golden brown on first side, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Remove sandwiches; add another @butter{1%tbsp} to pan. Once butter has melted, return sandwiches to pan and cook on second side until bread is golden brown and cheese has melted, ~{4-5%minutes} more.

> For 4 servings, cook in two batches; repeat process with remaining sandwiches, adding 1 TBSP butter to the pan for each side.

== Salad ==

While sandwiches cook, add @arugula{2%oz}, @dried cranberries{1%oz}, and @sunflower seeds{1/2%oz} to a #large bowl{}; toss with as much @honey Dijon dressing{1.5%oz} as you like. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Halve melts on a diagonal.

Divide salad and melts between plates. Serve with any remaining Honey Dijon Dressing on the side for dipping.